How far will that get me?

266
00:20:27,515 --> 00:20:30,813
Nick Savrinn.
His bar number is 56437.

267
00:20:30,858 --> 00:20:33,722
I've got a call time with my client,
an LJ Burrows.

268
00:20:39,468 --> 00:20:42,192
- Hello.
- Know who this is?

269
00:20:42,568 --> 00:20:43,353
Yeah.

270
00:20:44,195 --> 00:20:47,532
- Yeah. Nick Savrinn.
- How you holding on?

271
00:20:47,955 --> 00:20:51,583
Doing what I can do.
How about you?

272
00:20:52,508 --> 00:20:55,990
I'm worried about you. I'm sorry
about what you're going through.

273
00:20:56,087 --> 00:20:58,013
Thanks. Word is, uh...

274
00:20:58,108 --> 00:21:03,432
after this hearing, because of my
dad being so high profile, they're...

275
00:21:04,085 --> 00:21:07,470
they're shipping me to an adult
facility in Kingman, Arizona.

276
00:21:07,615 --> 00:21:10,480
Yeah, well, hopefully,
that ain't going to happen.

277
00:21:10,575 --> 00:21:12,552
You hear from Veronica today?

278
00:21:12,736 --> 00:21:16,261
She didn't show up.
They gave me some court-appointed clown.

279
00:21:17,107 --> 00:21:20,300
No. I haven't heard from her.

280
00:21:20,397 --> 00:21:21,563
Hey, this, uh...

281
00:21:21,706 --> 00:21:24,341
this fed came by and
talked to me today.

282
00:21:24,525 --> 00:21:25,270
Yeah?

283
00:21:25,417 --> 00:21:28,041
He wanted me to help try in
getting my dad to turn himself in.

284
00:21:28,075 --> 00:21:30,761
Well, knowing your dad,
I doubt that's going to happen.

285
00:21:30,796 --> 00:21:33,153
Listen up, LJ.
This is real important.

286
00:21:33,285 --> 00:21:34,322
All right.

287
00:21:34,456 --> 00:21:37,561
On the third,
look out for Otis Wright.

288
00:21:37,708 --> 00:21:41,940
You got that?
On the third, look out for Otis Wright.

289
00:21:42,086 --> 00:21:43,631
Until then, keep you head up.

290
00:21:43,726 --> 00:21:45,981
- What?
- Just remember that.

291
00:21:46,125 --> 00:21:48,111
I'm going to do everything
I can to get you out.

292
00:21:48,148 --> 00:21:51,773
Hey, Nick...
if you talk to my dad...

293
00:21:51,907 --> 00:21:54,261
tell him no matter what,
I love him.

294
00:22:01,018 --> 00:22:02,703
- Hey.
- Hey.

295
00:22:03,445 --> 00:22:06,363
- Did you get him?
- Let's do this.

296
00:22:07,898 --> 00:22:09,860
Got one more stop.

297
00:22:20,835 --> 00:22:23,633
There is a belief in my religion
which I know to be true

298
00:22:23,707 --> 00:22:27,040
and it applies to everyone,
Hindu or not.

299
00:22:27,506 --> 00:22:31,942
The acts we commit in this life
determine where we go in the next.

300
00:22:32,125 --> 00:22:36,320
And he who commits evil can
never hope for eternal happiness.

301
00:22:37,897 --> 00:22:42,230
Never been a goal of mine, doc.
I'm more a here and now type.

302
00:22:45,105 --> 00:22:47,831
I'll tell you something
I know is true.

303
00:22:47,926 --> 00:22:54,243
The Indians here, the Tomahawk variety,
some of them believe--

304
00:22:54,336 --> 00:22:57,542
well, used to believe before
most of them were slaughtered--

305
00:22:57,635 --> 00:23:02,913
that when a warrior
kills another in battle,

306
00:23:03,036 --> 00:23:08,882
he absorbs that fallen
warrior's spirit.

307
00:23:10,176 --> 00:23:13,572
So this isn't the
end for you, Doc.

308
00:23:15,835 --> 00:23:17,952
You're with me now.

309
00:24:28,798 --> 00:24:31,102
And how are you
doing this fine day?

310
00:24:31,427 --> 00:24:34,951
Uh, I'm great. How are you?

311
00:24:35,146 --> 00:24:38,441
Couldn't be better. Anything in
particular I can help you find?

312
00:24:38,678 --> 00:24:40,271
Just looking, thanks.

313
00:24:40,368 --> 00:24:43,020
Well, if you need any assistance,
just give a holler.

314
00:25:10,685 --> 00:25:12,990
- How are you this fine day?
- Great.

315
00:25:13,087 --> 00:25:16,192
- Can I help you find anything?
- I'm good, thanks.

316
00:25:21,148 --> 00:25:23,110
- Hey.
- We gotta go.

317
00:25:23,255 --> 00:25:25,460
- I just need to pay up.
- Now.

318
00:25:26,148 --> 00:25:28,020
How are you today, officer?

319
00:25:31,627 --> 00:25:33,841
Yeah, they were right, uh...

320
00:25:35,466 --> 00:25:38,090
Well, they were--
they were right back here.

321
00:25:43,096 --> 00:25:44,980
We can make it to the
courthouse on foot from here.

322
00:25:45,016 --> 00:25:47,842
You don't understand--
everything is in that car.

323
00:25:47,938 --> 00:25:51,463
Forget the damn car. We don't have time.
Come on, man, let's go.

324
00:26:10,908 --> 00:26:11,392
Hi.

325
00:26:49,616 --> 00:26:53,193
It is the finding of this
panel that Warden Pope,

326
00:26:53,295 --> 00:26:56,581
you'll be docked two weeks,
placed on three months probation.

327
00:26:58,116 --> 00:27:03,063
Officer Brad Bellick will be
terminated-- effectively immediately.

328
00:27:03,386 --> 00:27:06,412
Mr. Bellick, you can retrieve
whatever belongings you may have

329
00:27:06,446 --> 00:27:08,891
from Fox River;
that will be all.

330
00:27:09,726 --> 00:27:14,250
I've... I've worked at Fox
River since I was 18 years old.

331
00:27:14,345 --> 00:27:18,350
- Being a C.O. is my life.
- And we appreciate that.

332
00:27:18,397 --> 00:27:21,040
Look, you know, we could have saved
a lot of time if you would have

333
00:27:21,078 --> 00:27:24,060
just told us in the beginning that
this was going to be a railroad.

334
00:27:24,095 --> 00:27:24,851
That'll be all, Warden.

335
00:27:24,886 --> 00:27:27,570
There is only one person responsible
for this escape out there.

336
00:27:27,605 --> 00:27:31,373
His name is Michael Scofield.
It's not Officer Bellick. It's not me!

337
00:27:32,116 --> 00:27:34,611
But you need a fall guy, fine.

338
00:27:34,758 --> 00:27:37,490
But you're not gonna be just
taking Officer Bellick's job.

339
00:27:37,525 --> 00:27:40,540
Because even though I am not
proud of many of his actions,

340
00:27:40,675 --> 00:27:45,770
it will be a cold day in hell when
I turn my back on one of my own men.

341
00:27:46,235 --> 00:27:50,661
I quit. That will be all.

342
00:27:53,076 --> 00:27:56,741
If this thing doesn't work out and
you end up going back to Fox River,

343
00:27:56,836 --> 00:27:59,140
I ain't coming to get ya.

344
00:27:59,235 --> 00:28:03,142
I mean,
you are the brains and I am the brute.

345
00:28:08,978 --> 00:28:11,942
Seriously, Michael,
you don't have to do this.

346
00:28:24,665 --> 00:28:25,932
Let's go.

347
00:28:58,237 --> 00:28:59,831
We're good.

348
00:29:00,526 --> 00:29:02,682
You got a call from Nick
Savrinn earlier today.

349
00:29:02,715 --> 00:29:04,120
What was that all about?

350
00:29:04,916 --> 00:29:07,021
He's my attorney.
That's privileged.

351
00:29:07,127 --> 00:29:09,892
Hmm, that's odd because
Nick Savrinn was found dead

352
00:29:09,997 --> 00:29:13,312
in his apartment an hour before
that call came in to you.

353
00:29:13,916 --> 00:29:15,980
Listen up, LJ,
this is real important.

354
00:29:16,127 --> 00:29:16,630
All right.

355
00:29:16,727 --> 00:29:20,631
On the third, look out for Otis Wright.
You got that?

356
00:29:20,757 --> 00:29:22,302
You know for someone
who's so convinced that

357
00:29:22,335 --> 00:29:24,510
the government is capable of
so many underhanded things,

358
00:29:24,548 --> 00:29:27,361
you sure are playing
fast and loose with me.

359
00:29:27,465 --> 00:29:30,290
What are you going to do,
throw another fake murder charge on me?

360
00:29:30,328 --> 00:29:31,501
Who's Otis Wright?

361
00:29:32,057 --> 00:29:34,212
- I have no idea.
- I think you do.

362
00:29:34,306 --> 00:29:36,670
And if you don't tell me,
after you're convicted,

363
00:29:36,706 --> 00:29:38,780
I will be in that courtroom
when you're sentenced

364
00:29:38,818 --> 00:29:42,923
and I will hang you out to dry.
Take it to the bank.

365
00:30:29,916 --> 00:30:34,581
Yeah, put me in touch with the
prosecutor in the LJ Burrows case.

366
00:30:37,176 --> 00:30:38,632
I want a meeting.

367
00:30:44,366 --> 00:30:47,241
On the third,
look out for Otis Wright.

368
00:30:52,198 --> 00:30:54,120
Until then, keep your head up.

369
00:31:00,925 --> 00:31:02,490
Otis Wright.

370
00:31:03,398 --> 00:31:05,750
- Let's go.
- Hold on.

371
00:31:10,846 --> 00:31:12,952
- Move it.
- Hold on.

372
00:31:44,406 --> 00:31:45,853
I'll escort the boy.

373
00:31:56,215 --> 00:31:59,752
Otis Wright.
Otis elevator on the right.

374
00:32:00,035 --> 00:32:01,950
What is he planning?

375
00:32:03,297 --> 00:32:06,020
Keep it in the holster
and no one gets hurt.

376
00:32:07,418 --> 00:32:09,651
Keep it in the holster.

377
00:32:10,255 --> 00:32:13,270
All right, LJ, hit stop.

378
00:32:15,676 --> 00:32:17,323
He's coming with us.

379
00:32:17,458 --> 00:32:20,992
So just stay cool, stay cool.

380
00:32:22,197 --> 00:32:24,971
Hey, buddy, give me his gun.

381
00:32:29,228 --> 00:32:30,680
Hey, hey...

382
00:32:38,275 --> 00:32:40,081
LJ, give me your hand.

383
00:32:40,548 --> 00:32:42,801
That a boy. Come on.

384
00:32:50,118 --> 00:32:53,082
Hey, back off!
Back off! Back off!

385
00:32:53,177 --> 00:32:55,160
You're not shooting anybody,
neither are you.

386
00:32:55,196 --> 00:32:57,140
Give yourself up and
your kid can walk.

387
00:32:57,198 --> 00:32:59,020
It's the only way he's
getting out of this place.

388
00:32:59,058 --> 00:33:01,262
It's the only way!

389
00:33:01,586 --> 00:33:02,570
Dad!

390
00:33:08,955 --> 00:33:10,181
Dad, you got to let me go.

391
00:33:10,218 --> 00:33:11,902
- No.
- Dad...

392
00:33:15,838 --> 00:33:17,240
You got to let me go!

393
00:33:27,847 --> 00:33:30,471
Up there. Scofield is in the building.
Take him!

394
00:33:30,617 --> 00:33:35,512
You guys go, cover that way. Scofield
and Burrows are in the building!

395
00:33:41,767 --> 00:33:43,403
Freeze! Do not move!

396
00:33:43,507 --> 00:33:44,763
The truck!

397
00:34:45,108 --> 00:34:48,160
- Bradley?
- Yeah, Ma.

398
00:34:50,425 --> 00:34:52,162
What are you doing
home so early?

399
00:34:52,255 --> 00:34:53,712
I had to take...

400
00:34:54,267 --> 00:34:58,221
my personal day, you know,
before they went away.

401
00:34:59,478 --> 00:35:01,572
Shouldn't you be looking
for the convicts?

402
00:35:02,515 --> 00:35:05,761
They got somebody
else doing that, Mom.

403
00:35:05,995 --> 00:35:07,111
You okay?

404
00:35:18,085 --> 00:35:19,390
I'm good.

405
00:35:20,416 --> 00:35:21,352
Okay.

406
00:36:28,266 --> 00:36:32,361
Whoa. All right.

407
00:36:32,828 --> 00:36:35,660
I think we should break a bottle
of champagne across its bow.

408
00:36:35,696 --> 00:36:38,821
If you're intending to get this thing
home for your anniversary tonight,

409
00:36:38,857 --> 00:36:40,963
- I wouldn't recommend it.
