412
00:36:52,687 --> 00:36:54,283
I'm breaking out.

413
00:36:55,258 --> 00:36:58,291
And you're going to make sure
my brother goes with me.

414
00:38:17,686 --> 00:38:20,933
Thank you for calling AutoStar,
Dr... Gudat?

415
00:38:21,028 --> 00:38:22,710
Am I pronouncing
that correctly?

416
00:38:22,895 --> 00:38:24,822
Uh... dead on.

417
00:38:25,106 --> 00:38:26,741
How can I help you today?

418
00:38:27,207 --> 00:38:31,262
I need, uh... directions.

419
00:38:31,335 --> 00:38:33,781
- Where to, sir?
- Utah.

420
00:38:47,188 --> 00:38:48,213
Excuse me.

421
00:38:48,778 --> 00:38:51,870
I'm sorry.
Are you Scott Kolbrenner?

422
00:38:53,637 --> 00:38:55,840
I am. Yeah.

423
00:38:56,265 --> 00:38:58,311
You must be Debra Jean.

424
00:38:58,407 --> 00:39:00,453
- It's nice to meet you.
- Yes, same here.

425
00:39:00,478 --> 00:39:02,883
It's so funny, 'cause I was almost
ready to leave when you called.

426
00:39:02,918 --> 00:39:04,180
No one else responded.

427
00:39:04,275 --> 00:39:06,571
I guess there's not a lot
of Utah people out here.

428
00:39:06,607 --> 00:39:09,382
- Are you from there?
- No, I just, you know...

429
00:39:09,598 --> 00:39:14,120
I'm headed up there to, uh...
collect an inheritance.

430
00:39:14,306 --> 00:39:15,611
My grandpa died.

431
00:39:15,757 --> 00:39:17,391
Oh, I'm sorry to hear that.

432
00:39:17,538 --> 00:39:20,122
It's all right.
He went out with his boots on.

433
00:39:20,266 --> 00:39:24,363
- So where's your stuff?
